♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.712 --> 01:46.454
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:54.679 --> 01:56.507
BAYWATCH

02:01.991 --> 02:05.255
[SEAGULLS CRYING]

02:10.565 --> 02:12.784
"FATAL EXCHANGE"

02:37.418 --> 02:39.463
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

02:58.178 --> 02:59.527
[PANTING]

03:06.621 --> 03:07.709
HERE, BOY.

03:33.300 --> 03:35.519
PLEASE, ALLOW ME.

03:35.650 --> 03:37.869
THANK YOU.

03:42.309 --> 03:43.310
VOILA.

03:43.440 --> 03:44.354
OH.

03:53.363 --> 03:54.886
WHAT ARE YOU STARING AT?

03:55.017 --> 03:57.889
I JUST CAN'T GET OVER
HOW GREAT YOU LOOK.

04:00.109 --> 04:01.719
THIS IS REALLY PRETTY, MITCH.

04:02.677 --> 04:04.983
HOW DID YOU GET THIS
ALL ARRANGED?

04:05.593 --> 04:08.204
ONE OF THE BENEFITS
OF BEING A 20-YEAR LIFEGUARD.

04:08.335 --> 04:10.424
THE BEACH IS MY OFFICE.

04:11.729 --> 04:13.122
WILEY, TAKE IT EASY!

04:13.253 --> 04:14.471
NO WORRIES, MATE.

04:14.602 --> 04:15.820
I'M A NATURAL-BORN SEAMAN.

04:20.216 --> 04:21.957
RIDES LIKE THE WIND,
DON'T SHE, MATE?

04:22.740 --> 04:24.307
GOD,
IF I HAD ONE OF THESE BACK HOME,

04:24.438 --> 04:26.091
I'D TURN A FEW HEADS,
I TELL YOU.

04:28.050 --> 04:29.486
OH, SHE'S A BEAUT.

04:32.924 --> 04:33.838
[DOG BARKING]

04:38.234 --> 04:39.453
SO, WHAT YOU BEEN DOING

04:39.583 --> 04:41.019
SINCE THE WESTSIDE PRESS
WENT UNDER?

04:41.150 --> 04:43.195
I'VE BEEN DOING
A LOT OF TRAVELING,

04:43.326 --> 04:44.719
AND, UH...

04:44.849 --> 04:46.111
I STARTED A NOVEL.

04:46.242 --> 04:48.070
-YEAH?
-BUT THEN I RAN OUT OF MONEY,

04:48.200 --> 04:50.594
SO I JUST KIND OF GOT BACK
INTO THE FREELANCING.

04:51.247 --> 04:52.248
SO WHAT ABOUT YOU?

04:52.379 --> 04:54.032
OH, AND HOW'S HOBIE?

04:54.642 --> 04:57.558
HOBIE IS APPROACHING PUBERTY
AT BREAKNECK SPEED.

04:59.124 --> 05:00.300
WELL, THAT SOUNDS LIKE TROUBLE.

05:00.909 --> 05:02.345
YOU KNOW, KAY,
IT'S A LOT DIFFERENT OUT THERE

05:02.476 --> 05:03.477
THAN WHEN WE WERE KIDS.

05:04.347 --> 05:06.175
YOU KNOW FRANKLY, I DON'T KNOW
HOW MY MOM AND DAD DID IT.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.221
MAYBE IT'S BECAUSE
I HAD A MOM AND DAD, I MEAN...

05:11.702 --> 05:13.095
I REALLY THINK HOBIE MISSES

05:13.225 --> 05:15.315
THAT STRONG FEMALE PRESENCE
IN HIS LIFE.

05:15.924 --> 05:17.534
OH, I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT,
MITCH.

05:17.665 --> 05:20.581
I THINK-- I THINK HOBIE'S
A WELL-ADJUSTED KID.

05:21.843 --> 05:23.366
AS OPPOSED TO HIS FATHER.

05:25.977 --> 05:27.327
CHEERS.

05:33.202 --> 05:35.117
MITCH, THERE'S A DOG OUT THERE.

05:38.512 --> 05:39.817
HE LOOKS LIKE
HE'S CAUGHT IN A RIP.

05:39.948 --> 05:41.123
I'M SORRY, UH...

05:41.645 --> 05:42.429
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

05:42.559 --> 05:46.433
LIFEGUARD BAYWATCH

05:48.348 --> 05:50.350
WILEY, OVER THERE!

05:50.480 --> 05:52.221
THERE'S A DOG IN THE WATER.

05:57.357 --> 05:58.793
HELP! MY DOG!

05:59.576 --> 06:01.186
IT'S ALL RIGHT. TAKE IT EASY.
DON'T PANIC.

06:01.491 --> 06:02.840
IT'S OKAY.

06:03.363 --> 06:04.625
YOU GOT TO GET MY DOG.

06:04.755 --> 06:05.713
WE WILL.

06:10.239 --> 06:11.806
OH, MAN, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

06:11.936 --> 06:13.111
TAKE THE WHEEL, MATE.

06:13.808 --> 06:15.592
COME ON. GOOD ON YA.

06:19.074 --> 06:22.077
LOS ANGELES COUNTY
LIFEGUARD

06:22.207 --> 06:24.296
[SIRENS BLARING]

06:36.874 --> 06:37.745
MITCH!

06:38.659 --> 06:39.790
IS SHE OKAY?

06:39.921 --> 06:41.792
YEAH, SHE'S ALL RIGHT.

06:41.923 --> 06:43.968
SHE'S OKAY. BE RIGHT BACK.

06:48.843 --> 06:49.670
WHO IS THAT?

06:50.366 --> 06:51.454
WILEY BROWN,

06:52.194 --> 06:54.892
OUR NEW EXCHANGE LIFEGUARD
FROM THE LAND DOWN UNDER.

06:55.023 --> 06:57.373
WHOO-WHEE!

07:01.203 --> 07:02.639
COME ON, BABY.

07:03.771 --> 07:06.556
SORT OF A CROSS BETWEEN
MEL GIBSON AND CROCODILE DUNDEE.

07:08.166 --> 07:09.646
COME ON, BABY.

07:09.777 --> 07:12.257
WHOO-WHEE!

07:12.388 --> 07:13.998
HEY, HEY, HEY!

07:18.220 --> 07:20.788
YOU DID IT. YOU CAUGHT HIM.

07:20.918 --> 07:22.180
COME ON, MATE.

07:22.311 --> 07:24.052
LOOK AT THE SIZE
OF THIS BLOODY DINGO.

07:34.758 --> 07:35.759
UNBELIEVABLE.

07:53.255 --> 07:54.691
-HERE YOU GO, DARLING.
-STAR!

07:55.431 --> 07:57.215
COMPLIMENTS OF THE LAND
DOWN UNDER.

08:00.349 --> 08:02.656
WILEY BROWN, AT YOUR SERVICE.

08:04.005 --> 08:06.311
YOU'VE GOT TO ADMIT,
WILEY'S GOT A UNIQUE STYLE.

08:06.442 --> 08:07.922
YEAH,

08:08.052 --> 08:09.880
SURE KNOWS HOW TO DRAW A CROWD,
DOESN'T HE?

08:10.011 --> 08:12.230
OH, MITCH,
STOP BEING SO CYNICAL.

08:12.361 --> 08:13.797
HOW IS THAT BEING CYNICAL?

08:14.406 --> 08:16.583
THAT WASN'T A RESCUE,
THAT WAS A CIRCUS ACT.

08:16.713 --> 08:18.933
ALL HE HAD TO DO WAS SCOOP
THAT DOG UP WITH A NET.

08:20.021 --> 08:21.370
YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK
THE REAL PROBLEM IS?

08:21.979 --> 08:23.851
NO, I DON'T.
WHY DON'T YOU ENLIGHTEN ME?

08:24.416 --> 08:26.244
YOU GUYS ARE TWO PEAS IN A POD.

08:26.854 --> 08:28.769
THE LAST
OF THE RUGGED INDIVIDUALISTS.

08:29.378 --> 08:31.772
BRAVE, COURAGEOUS, AND BOLD.

08:32.903 --> 08:35.123
WILEY BROWN'S JUST
THE AUSTRALIAN MITCH BUCHANNON,

08:35.732 --> 08:38.386
SO IT'S ONLY NATURAL
YOU TWO WOULD BUTT HEADS.

08:38.518 --> 08:40.476
SO YOU THINK
IT'S A MALE EGO THING, HUH?

08:41.433 --> 08:42.957
BASICALLY, YES.

08:43.087 --> 08:45.307
WELL, THAT JUST GOES TO SHOW YOU
HOW WRONG YOU ARE.

08:45.437 --> 08:48.484
MY PROBLEM WITH THIS GUY
IS PURELY PROFESSIONAL.

08:48.615 --> 08:50.094
HE'S MORE INTERESTED
IN SHOWING OFF

08:50.225 --> 08:51.922
THAN BEING
A RESPONSIBLE LIFEGUARD.

08:52.532 --> 08:53.794
I'M TELLING YOU,

08:53.924 --> 08:55.317
YOU KEEP AN EYE ON HIM
WHILE HE'S HERE.

08:55.447 --> 08:57.014
SEE YOU LATER, EVERYONE.

08:57.145 --> 08:58.625
[APPLAUSE AND CHEERS]

08:59.495 --> 09:00.757
I GOT NO PROBLEM WITH THAT.

09:00.888 --> 09:02.890
"I GOT NO PROBLEM..."
I NEED THIS.

09:03.020 --> 09:04.544
[LAUGHS]

09:06.546 --> 09:08.286
LET'S CHECK THAT DUTY ROSTER.

09:08.417 --> 09:09.244
G'DAY.

09:09.374 --> 09:10.898
-HI.
-OH, HI.

09:14.292 --> 09:15.555
AND WHERE IS MY MATE?

09:16.686 --> 09:17.992
YO, MATT.

09:18.122 --> 09:19.559
YO, WILEY.

09:20.734 --> 09:22.126
-THERE YOU ARE.
-HOW ARE YOU, MAN?

09:22.257 --> 09:23.737
LOOK, MATE,
I WAS HOPING YOU'D HELP ME

09:23.867 --> 09:25.129
WITH THAT INCIDENT REPORT TODAY.

09:25.260 --> 09:26.566
WELL, I'M NOT TOO HANDY

09:26.696 --> 09:28.219
WITH YOUR YANK LINGO JUST YET,
AM I?

09:28.350 --> 09:29.830
NO PROBLEM, MAN.
I'LL GET RIGHT ON IT.

09:29.960 --> 09:31.745
OH, BEAUT. GOOD ON YA.

09:31.875 --> 09:33.398
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE A LIGHT,
WOULD YOU?

09:33.529 --> 09:35.357
WE'RE NOT ALLOWED TO SMOKE
IN THE HEADQUARTERS.

09:35.966 --> 09:38.099
YOU'RE ALSO NOT SUPPOSED
TO WEAR A TOWEL IN THE LOUNGE.

09:38.882 --> 09:41.058
ALL RIGHTY.
HAVE IT YOUR WAY, DARLING.

09:41.189 --> 09:42.712
NO, I MEAN, YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO WEAR CLOTHES

09:42.843 --> 09:44.105
OR A BATHING SUIT.

09:44.758 --> 09:46.803
YEAH. WELL, FIRST THINGS FIRST,
EH, LOVE?

09:46.934 --> 09:48.762
YEAH. I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

09:48.892 --> 09:50.590
LOOK, MATE, CAN YOU HELP ME OUT
WITH SOME CHANGE FOR A SODA?

09:50.720 --> 09:52.113
I'M A LITTLE SHORT.

09:52.243 --> 09:53.723
AS USUAL.

09:58.119 --> 09:59.120
OOH-OOH-OOH.

09:59.250 --> 10:00.817
HI, SUMMER. HAVE YOU SEEN MITCH?

10:00.948 --> 10:02.297
YEAH,
HE SHOULD BE DOWN IN A MINUTE.

10:02.427 --> 10:03.341
OKAY, THANKS.

10:03.472 --> 10:05.387
I BET SHE'LL BE SPUNKY, MATE.

10:06.301 --> 10:07.302
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

10:15.615 --> 10:16.877
G'DAY.

10:17.007 --> 10:18.356
HELLO.

10:18.487 --> 10:19.923
I SAW YOU ON THE BEACH
WITH A CAMERA.

10:20.054 --> 10:21.577
SO, I GUESS
YOU'RE WITH THE PRESS, EH?

10:21.708 --> 10:24.188
NO WORRIES, LOVE,
I'D NEVER HOLD IT AGAINST YOU.

10:25.363 --> 10:27.104
OH, THAT'S SO REASSURING.

10:28.932 --> 10:30.281
THE NAME'S WILEY BROWN.

10:31.413 --> 10:32.240
AND YOU ARE?

10:32.370 --> 10:34.242
THE NAME'S KAY MORGAN.

10:34.372 --> 10:35.765
GOOD TO KNOW YOU, KAY.

10:37.506 --> 10:38.942
SO, YOU WANT TO DO THE STORY

10:39.073 --> 10:40.596
ON THE STRANGER
FROM THE STRANGE LAND, EH?

10:40.727 --> 10:42.076
IS THERE A STORY THERE?

10:42.206 --> 10:45.383
A STORY? MORE LIKE
A BLOODY LEGEND, DARLIN'.

10:45.514 --> 10:48.343
NOW, WHAT DO YOU WANT
TO HEAR ABOUT? HUH?

10:49.605 --> 10:51.302
HOW ABOUT THE TIME...

10:51.738 --> 10:54.262
I PULLED A DINGO
OUT OF A QUICKSAND SWAMP, HUH?

10:58.353 --> 11:00.094
NO, WAIT.

11:00.224 --> 11:02.836
THE TIME THE BLUEYS RAIDED
THE TOPLESS BEACH AT TAMARAMA.

11:03.706 --> 11:06.143
NOW, THERE'S A DAY THAT WON'T SO
ON BE FORGOTTEN, DARLIN'.

11:12.106 --> 11:13.411
SO...

11:17.372 --> 11:18.373
-I'LL SEE YOU LATER.
-OKAY.

11:23.073 --> 11:24.031
HEY, MITCH.

11:24.161 --> 11:24.814
HEY, MATT, WHAT'S HAPPENING?

11:24.945 --> 11:26.294
HOW YOU DOING?

11:26.424 --> 11:27.556
LISTEN,
CAN I BORROW SOME AFTERSHAVE?

11:27.687 --> 11:28.731
YEAH, SURE. HELP YOURSELF.

11:28.862 --> 11:29.689
-THE LOCKER'S OPEN.
-THANKS.

11:31.908 --> 11:32.953
-OH, MY GOD!
-DON'T MOVE.

11:35.956 --> 11:37.348
DON'T MOVE.

11:37.479 --> 11:39.089
[HISSING, RATTLING]

11:42.832 --> 11:44.312
CLEMENTINE...

11:45.008 --> 11:46.357
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
OUT OF YOUR SACK?

11:54.539 --> 11:55.976
SORRY ABOUT THAT.

11:57.281 --> 11:59.066
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING
WITH A SNAKE AT HEADQUARTERS?

11:59.196 --> 12:02.112
OH, NO WORRIES, MATE.
SHE'S NOT POISONOUS.

12:02.243 --> 12:04.375
JUST A LITTLE FRISKY,
THAT'S ALL.

12:04.506 --> 12:05.768
HEY, CLEMENTINE.

12:08.466 --> 12:09.946
COME ON, DARLIN'. IN YOU GO.

12:16.561 --> 12:17.606
COME ON, DARLIN'.

12:19.651 --> 12:20.783
IN YOU GO.

12:33.622 --> 12:36.146
HOW DID WILEY GET TOWER 18?

12:36.930 --> 12:37.713
[SCOFFS]

12:37.844 --> 12:38.888
BECAUSE...

12:39.933 --> 12:40.890
HE GAVE ME THIS.

12:43.458 --> 12:45.982
OH, TAKING BRIBES.
THAT'S A NICE PRECEDENT.

12:46.113 --> 12:47.505
OH, MITCH, COME ON,
IT WASN'T A BRIBE,

12:47.636 --> 12:48.985
IT WAS A GIFT.

12:49.116 --> 12:50.291
ANYWAY,
HE'S NOT OUT THERE BY HIMSELF.

12:50.421 --> 12:51.988
I'M DOUBLING UP WITH HIM.

12:52.119 --> 12:52.902
OF COURSE.

12:53.033 --> 12:54.251
GOOD MORNING.

12:54.382 --> 12:55.426
-HEY, KAY.
-HI.

12:55.557 --> 12:57.211
HI. WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

12:57.341 --> 12:58.778
WELL, YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO BELIEVE THIS,

12:58.908 --> 13:00.214
BUT YOU KNOW
THOSE PICTURES I TOOK

13:00.344 --> 13:02.085
OF WILEY SAVING THE DOG?

13:02.216 --> 13:04.784
WELL, I SHOWED IT TO THE EDITOR
AT THE MALIBU MAGAZINE,

13:05.349 --> 13:07.264
AND SHE WANTS ME TO DO
A FEATURE STORY ON HIM

13:07.395 --> 13:08.439
FOR THE NEXT ISSUE.

13:08.570 --> 13:09.963
-ALL RIGHT!
-THANK YOU.

13:10.093 --> 13:11.965
-CONGRATULATIONS.
-OH, WELL, THANK YOU.

13:12.095 --> 13:13.705
IT'S NOT GOING TO WIN A PULITZER
OR ANYTHING,

13:13.836 --> 13:16.447
-BUT IT PAYS THE RENT.
-I GOT TO GO.

13:16.578 --> 13:17.709
I'LL CATCH YOU LATER.

13:20.103 --> 13:22.279
WAS IT SOMETHING I SAID? UM...

13:22.410 --> 13:23.803
NOPE. MEN.

13:31.985 --> 13:33.377
LIFEGUARD

13:33.508 --> 13:35.640
THERE YOU GO, MATE.
AS FRESH AS A DAISY.

13:35.771 --> 13:37.425
NO SNAKES
IN THE GLOVE COMPARTMENT?

13:37.555 --> 13:39.166
[CHUCKLES]

13:39.296 --> 13:41.124
SHE'S HOME UNDER LOCK AND KEY.

13:42.212 --> 13:43.431
SO, LIEUTENANT...

13:43.561 --> 13:44.954
WHAT DO YOU YANKS CALL

13:45.085 --> 13:46.913
THOSE LITTLE BUGGERS
THAT EAT THROUGH WOOD?

13:47.565 --> 13:48.784
TERMITES.

13:48.915 --> 13:50.830
TERMITES. YEAH, THAT'S IT.

13:52.440 --> 13:54.007
WHY DO YOU WANT TO KNOW
ABOUT TERMITES?

13:54.877 --> 13:57.532
WELL, BACK HOME,
WE CALL THEM WHITE ANTS,

13:58.098 --> 14:00.056
BUT WE USE THE TERM
IN ANOTHER WAY, AS WELL.

14:00.970 --> 14:02.450
NOW, A WHITE ANT

14:02.580 --> 14:04.452
IS A BLOKE THAT STEALS
ANOTHER BLOKE'S BIRD,

14:04.582 --> 14:07.368
AND THAT AIN'T ME, IS IT?
NO, SIR, THAT AIN'T ME.

14:08.325 --> 14:10.023
SO, I WANTED TO SET IT
STRAIGHT WITH YOU

14:10.545 --> 14:12.025
BEFORE I HAD A GO AT KAY.

14:15.855 --> 14:17.291
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO ASK MY PERMISSION

14:17.421 --> 14:18.683
TO HAVE A GO AT HER.

14:19.554 --> 14:20.772
KAY'S NOT MY BIRD.

14:20.903 --> 14:22.078
SUPER.

14:26.169 --> 14:27.605
THEN EVERYTHING'S APPLES, EH?

14:27.736 --> 14:30.043
LOOK, ALL I'M INTERESTED IN
IS YOU DOING YOUR JOB.

14:30.173 --> 14:32.393
WHAT YOU DO ON YOUR OWN TIME
IS YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

14:33.568 --> 14:34.569
FAIR ENOUGH, MATE.

14:35.352 --> 14:36.440
HAVE A NICE DAY.

14:47.582 --> 14:51.064
LIFEGUARD

15:05.817 --> 15:07.210
SEE, BACK IN AUSTRALIA, DARLING,

15:07.341 --> 15:09.125
EVERYBODY WANTS
TO COME TO MALIBU,

15:09.256 --> 15:10.866
YOU KNOW, SURF CITY.

15:10.997 --> 15:13.173
"TWO GIRLS FOR EVERY BOY"
AND ALL THAT.

15:14.000 --> 15:15.740
WELL, HAS IT LIVED UP
TO YOUR EXPECTATIONS?

15:17.481 --> 15:18.918
HAS IT EVER.

15:19.048 --> 15:20.615
I JUST WISH
I COULD STAY HERE FULL-TIME.

15:21.833 --> 15:23.096
THAT WOULD BE SWEET,
WOULDN'T IT?

15:23.226 --> 15:24.314
[CHUCKLES]

15:24.445 --> 15:26.360
-HUH?
-OH, YES, YES, YES.

15:26.490 --> 15:27.970
DID I EVER TELL YOU
ABOUT THE KANGAROO STORY?

15:28.101 --> 15:29.667
NO, NO. I DON'T EVEN KNOW
IF I'M READY FOR IT.

15:29.798 --> 15:30.842
COME ON, I GOT TO TELL YOU THAT.

15:30.973 --> 15:32.322
OKAY, OKAY.

15:48.773 --> 15:49.644
HEY, MITCH.

15:50.732 --> 15:52.603
I THOUGHT YOU WERE DOUBLING UP
WITH WILEY.

15:53.387 --> 15:54.605
RIGHT AFTER MY WORKOUT.

16:00.916 --> 16:02.874
YOU NEVER TOLD ME YOU USED
TO GO OUT WITH KAY MORGAN.

16:03.701 --> 16:04.964
WELL, YOU NEVER ASKED.

16:06.487 --> 16:07.662
SHE SEEMS REALLY NICE.

16:07.792 --> 16:10.273
YEAH, SHE IS...REAL NICE.

16:17.237 --> 16:18.978
ANOTHER REASON
TO HATE WILEY BROWN?

16:20.022 --> 16:21.719
KAY AND I ARE JUST FRIENDS.

16:21.850 --> 16:23.634
WE ONLY WENT OUT
A COUPLE OF TIMES.

16:24.244 --> 16:26.246
STILL, YOU'VE GOT TO ADMIT,

16:26.376 --> 16:28.248
SEEING HER WITH WILEY
ADDS A LITTLE FUEL TO THE FIRE.

16:28.378 --> 16:29.336
I NEED THIS.

16:29.945 --> 16:31.164
HEY, HEY, LOOK.

16:31.294 --> 16:32.730
I THOUGHT WE WERE FRIENDS.

16:32.861 --> 16:34.471
WE CAN TALK ABOUT OUR PROBLEMS.

16:34.602 --> 16:37.126
I DON'T HAVE A PROBLEM!
WHAT PROBLEM? WHAT PROBLEM?

16:37.257 --> 16:39.520
SOMETHING HAS GOT YOU
OFF YOUR GAME.

16:40.086 --> 16:41.391
I THINK IT'S WILEY.

16:41.913 --> 16:43.263
NOW,
IF YOU QUESTION HIS ABILITY,

16:43.393 --> 16:44.829
DON'T TRUST HIM, WHATEVER IT IS,

16:44.960 --> 16:46.875
I'LL CALL CHIEF THORPE
AND HAVE HIM REASSIGNED.

16:49.834 --> 16:50.966
YOU DON'T HAVE TO CALL ANYBODY.

16:51.097 --> 16:52.141
I'M SORRY.

16:55.057 --> 16:56.580
WILEY'S NOT MY PROBLEM.

16:59.496 --> 17:00.802
THEN WHAT IS IT?

17:03.805 --> 17:06.242
IT'S ABOUT A DREAM
I STARTED HAVING AGAIN.

17:11.638 --> 17:13.205
STEPHANIE, TEN YEARS AGO...

17:14.990 --> 17:17.601
I WENT TO AUSTRALIA
ON A LIFEGUARD EXCHANGE PROGRAM.

17:18.211 --> 17:20.126
I WAS WORKING A TOWER
AT BONDI BEACH.

17:20.256 --> 17:22.998
THAT'S THE HAPPENING BEACH
JUST OUTSIDE OF SYDNEY...

17:24.391 --> 17:27.133
WHEN A WINDSURFER WENT DOWN
JUST OFF THE PIER.

17:29.700 --> 17:33.878
BY THE TIME I GOT TO HER...
SHE WAS PROBABLY ALREADY DEAD.

17:34.009 --> 17:35.228
I MEAN, SHE WASN'T BREATHING.

17:37.099 --> 17:38.492
THAT WASN'T MY CONCERN.

17:38.622 --> 17:41.495
MY CONCERN WAS GETTING HER IN.

17:43.062 --> 17:44.367
THE WAVES WERE HUGE THAT DAY.

17:45.716 --> 17:47.588
WE GOT TOSSED AROUND
LIKE A PING-PONG BALL.

17:52.593 --> 17:54.029
I KNEW SOONER OR LATER

17:54.160 --> 17:56.162
WE WERE GOING TO SMASH
INTO ONE OF THE PILINGS.

17:58.207 --> 17:59.687
WHAT'S THE LIFEGUARD MANUAL
TELL YOU TO DO

17:59.817 --> 18:01.254
IN A SITUATION LIKE THAT?

18:01.384 --> 18:04.779
WELL, PUT THE VICTIM
BETWEEN YOURSELF AND THE PILING.

18:05.997 --> 18:07.521
IF YOU GET HURT,
YOU CAN'T COMPLETE THE RESCUE.

18:08.478 --> 18:09.566
THEY TEACH US
THAT IN ROOKIE SCHOOL.

18:10.524 --> 18:11.351
ABSOLUTELY.

18:13.918 --> 18:15.137
YOU EVER TRY THAT IN REALITY?

18:16.269 --> 18:17.226
NO.

18:18.706 --> 18:19.620
DOESN'T WORK THAT WAY.

18:20.664 --> 18:21.709
THERE'S NO WAY

18:22.492 --> 18:24.146
I WAS GOING TO USE THAT GIRL
AS A SHIELD.

18:26.148 --> 18:27.628
SO I TOOK THE BLOW.

18:30.979 --> 18:31.936
I WAS KNOCKED OUT.

18:36.941 --> 18:38.073
WHEN I CAME TO...

18:39.770 --> 18:41.424
I LOST THE GIRL.

18:41.555 --> 18:43.296
I HAD NO IDEA WHERE SHE WAS.

18:45.820 --> 18:48.866
CORONER'S REPORT SAID
IT WASN'T DROWNING,

18:48.997 --> 18:51.434
THAT THE OFFICIAL CAUSE OF DEATH
WAS HEMORRHAGING

18:51.565 --> 18:53.349
DUE TO THE MAST HITTING HER
ON THE HEAD.

18:55.612 --> 18:56.874
BUT FROM THAT DAY ON,

18:57.397 --> 18:59.268
THE WHOLE TIME
I WAS IN AUSTRALIA

18:59.399 --> 19:03.054
EVERY SINGLE DAY,
EVERY PLACE I WENT...

19:04.621 --> 19:05.970
I SAW THAT GIRL'S FACE.

19:11.933 --> 19:13.021
ANYWAY...

19:14.979 --> 19:16.285
I GOT BACK TO L.A.

19:17.460 --> 19:19.767
I FIGURED I'D BETTER BLOCK
THIS WHOLE THING OUT OF MY MIND

19:19.897 --> 19:21.203
OR ELSE GET A NEW CAREER.

19:23.597 --> 19:25.251
SO I ERASED IT FROM MY MEMORY.

19:29.820 --> 19:31.518
I EVEN MANAGED
TO FORGET HER NAME.

19:34.521 --> 19:36.000
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

19:38.786 --> 19:39.874
IT WAS SHEILA GOLD.

19:42.137 --> 19:45.619
MITCH, IF SHE WAS DEAD
BY THE TIME THAT YOU GOT TO HER,

19:45.749 --> 19:47.273
YOU CAN'T BLAME YOURSELF.

19:48.535 --> 19:49.362
YEAH, I KNOW.

19:49.884 --> 19:50.754
I KNOW.

19:52.843 --> 19:54.758
THAT'S WHY I THINK
I GOT A PROBLEM WITH WILEY.

19:54.889 --> 19:58.066
I MEAN,
EVERY TIME I LOOK AT HIM...

20:00.111 --> 20:01.200
IT JUST BRINGS UP THAT MEMORY.

20:03.289 --> 20:04.855
HE'LL ONLY BE HERE A MONTH.

20:04.986 --> 20:06.074
YEAH.

20:08.032 --> 20:08.816
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

20:08.946 --> 20:09.860
NO PROBLEM.

20:11.775 --> 20:12.689
NO PROBLEM AT ALL.

20:14.213 --> 20:16.258
HELL,
WE'LL PROBABLY BE BEST FRIENDS

20:16.389 --> 20:17.607
AT THE END OF THE MONTH, HUH?

20:49.596 --> 20:51.815
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

21:07.309 --> 21:09.355
